Over 30 armed mobile police men are reported to have stormed the Abuja resident of Senator Dino Melaye on Monday. The Senator who revealed this via his twitter handle@dino_melaye also said that all roads leading to his house in Maitama has been condoned off by the policemen. “Over 30 heavily armed fierce looking mobile police men have just stormed my residence in Maitama, Abuja. All roads leading to the house has been condoned off, as heavy mobile police men blocked entry and exit of the road. They currently laid siege on in and around the house,” he said. It would be recalled that Senator Melaye was on Monday morning arrested at the Abuja International Airport on his way out of the country.  